relevant_findings.General: Agitated with mild full body shakes, but able to answer questions.
relevant_findings.HEENT: PERRL, EOMI. No scleral icterus or conjunctival injection. Mucous membranes moist. No oral ulcers.
relevant_findings.Neck: Supple, no lymphadenopathy, no JVP elevation.
relevant_findings.Lungs: Poor effort but clear; no crackles, mild expiratory wheezing.
relevant_findings.Cardiovascular: Regular rate and rhythm, no murmurs, rubs, or gallops.
relevant_findings.Abdomen: Soft/obese, diffuse tenderness to palpation (possible greatest in epigastrium), urostomy intact with clear output, no distension, normal bowel sounds.
relevant_findings.Extremities: Warm and well perfused, with trace bilateral edema.
relevant_findings.Neurological: Minimal strength below waist (no change), not completely cooperative due to agitation but able to answer questions fluently.
